00:25:27,360 --> 00:25:31,072
<i>He didn't want
to blend in the group,</i>

474
00:25:31,155 --> 00:25:33,032
<i>but the group to accommodate</i>

475
00:25:33,532 --> 00:25:36,452
<i>to his way of being,
thinking, playing.</i>

476
00:25:36,619 --> 00:25:39,747
There were many unspoken clashes,

477
00:25:39,830 --> 00:25:41,332
but of course there were clashes.

478
00:25:41,415 --> 00:25:43,626
I remember a National Team player

479
00:25:43,709 --> 00:25:47,755
said before the World Cup,
"Hugo come, let's see what he finds."

480
00:25:51,676 --> 00:25:53,261
<i>He took a Spanish accent.</i>

481
00:25:54,971 --> 00:25:57,139
That annoyed some teammates.

482
00:25:58,557 --> 00:25:59,976
Even the coach.

483
00:26:02,270 --> 00:26:03,938
<i>He asked me to talk to him,</i>

484
00:26:05,564 --> 00:26:09,151
which I found to be
a ridiculous request,

485
00:26:09,235 --> 00:26:12,029
because it was like
not respecting

486
00:26:13,781 --> 00:26:14,907
the way he was.

487
00:26:14,991 --> 00:26:16,575
{\an8}Bora gave instructions,

488
00:26:16,659 --> 00:26:18,160
{\an8}"We'll run this way,"

489
00:26:18,244 --> 00:26:20,663
{\an8}and Hugo,
and I'm telling the truth,

490
00:26:21,205 --> 00:26:24,208
naturally said,
"Bora, can I make a suggest?

491
00:26:24,292 --> 00:26:26,127
In Real Madrid,
Butragueño gives me the ball

492
00:26:26,210 --> 00:26:27,670
and I rely on Michel,
who centers."

493
00:26:27,753 --> 00:26:30,339
The group said, "Son of a gun!

494
00:26:30,756 --> 00:26:32,008
What's with this guy?"

495
00:26:32,341 --> 00:26:35,553
<i>Hugo, as an icon, arrived</i>

496
00:26:37,054 --> 00:26:38,848
{\an8}acting like team captain.

497
00:26:38,931 --> 00:26:40,308
{\an8}He deserved it.

498
00:26:40,391 --> 00:26:43,227
{\an8}But there were people who had

499
00:26:43,686 --> 00:26:46,564
{\an8}worked for three years,
like Tomas Boy.

500
00:26:47,565 --> 00:26:50,901
<i>They asked me to please,</i>

501
00:26:51,277 --> 00:26:54,822
<i>be more humble, down to earth,</i>

502
00:26:54,905 --> 00:26:57,658
<i>they said they talked</i>

503
00:26:57,742 --> 00:27:00,411
<i>and that I wouldn't be made
team captain,</i>

504
00:27:00,494 --> 00:27:03,706
<i>because, if I was made team captain,</i>

505
00:27:04,165 --> 00:27:07,126
<i>there would be
more envy and jealousy.</i>

506
00:27:07,668 --> 00:27:10,588
It's unbelievable
they didn't let me be captain

507
00:27:11,630 --> 00:27:14,216
because of their mentality
and jealousy.

508
00:27:14,425 --> 00:27:18,429
I think they should have
asked me politely

509
00:27:18,763 --> 00:27:20,723
to be the leader, the captain,

510
00:27:20,806 --> 00:27:24,477
because I was succeeding
outside of Mexico.

511
00:27:26,103 --> 00:27:29,357
<i>Tomas was the captain
who wore the badge,</i>

512
00:27:29,899 --> 00:27:33,402
<i>and we sat down
and I remember that in that meeting</i>

513
00:27:33,652 --> 00:27:36,280
<i>Tomas and I commented</i>

514
00:27:36,447 --> 00:27:39,075
<i>that the group was a little restless</i>

515
00:27:39,158 --> 00:27:41,410
<i>regarding Hugo's behavior.</i>

516
00:27:42,620 --> 00:27:44,080
<i>And Hugo</i>

517
00:27:44,747 --> 00:27:46,290
<i>said the same.
"This is sad.</i>

518
00:27:46,999 --> 00:27:50,044
I thought it was a different group,"
he expressed,

519
00:27:50,127 --> 00:27:52,630
because he had been
in two previous

520
00:27:52,713 --> 00:27:53,714
World Cups, '78 and '82,

521
00:27:53,798 --> 00:27:56,133
where he perceived,
I wasn't there,

522
00:27:56,509 --> 00:28:00,179
factions, jealousy,
insecurities, small team,

523
00:28:00,554 --> 00:28:04,225
and he clashed with that,
and he felt that '86 was,

524
00:28:04,475 --> 00:28:07,395
<i>finally, a competitive, winning,</i>

525
00:28:07,478 --> 00:28:08,604
<i>protagonist team.</i>

526
00:28:09,980 --> 00:28:12,733
<i>The World Cup '86 is for Hugo</i>

527
00:28:12,817 --> 00:28:14,527
the Cup at home,
where he is and idol,

528
00:28:14,610 --> 00:28:16,028
and he's expected,

529
00:28:16,195 --> 00:28:19,949
and he arrives with an injury
from a game in Europe.

530
00:28:20,032 --> 00:28:23,577
<i>He had a different commitment
from everyone else.</i>

531
00:28:23,661 --> 00:28:27,206
So, surely,
the coaching team decided that Hugo

532
00:28:27,289 --> 00:28:29,166
would be granted
certain concessions.

533
00:28:30,918 --> 00:28:32,461
<i>They were asking me to lower</i>

534
00:28:32,545 --> 00:28:34,839
<i>my performance to their level.</i>

535
00:28:34,922 --> 00:28:39,176
And I said, "Why don't you
rise up to my mentality,

536
00:28:39,260 --> 00:28:40,845
my football level,

537
00:28:41,262 --> 00:28:44,098
<i>and that leadership I've earned,</i>

538
00:28:44,181 --> 00:28:45,516
<i>why don't you have it too?"</i>

539
00:28:45,641 --> 00:28:47,768
<i>He said, "It's too hard.</i>

540
00:28:47,852 --> 00:28:49,603
<i>We are not like you.</i>

541
00:28:49,854 --> 00:28:52,231
<i>We are limited
and we have problems."</i>

542
00:28:52,314 --> 00:28:55,317
<i>I said, "That's not my problem.
It's you problem."</i>

543
00:28:55,651 --> 00:28:57,069
Hugo was here

544
00:28:57,862 --> 00:28:58,988
at that time

545
00:28:59,947 --> 00:29:01,449
and the rest of us were here.

546
00:29:01,866 --> 00:29:03,534
There was no one here

547
00:29:03,617 --> 00:29:06,245
in the middle, or close

548
00:29:06,328 --> 00:29:09,874
to Hugo in that competition sense.

549
00:29:10,833 --> 00:29:12,376
<i>Hugo, you have to understand</i>

550
00:29:12,585 --> 00:29:17,173
<i>that we decided
that the eldest is the captain.</i>

551
00:29:17,631 --> 00:29:20,384
We think it's the most convenient.

552
00:29:20,634 --> 00:29:23,971
The eldest, back then,
was Tomas Boy.

553
00:29:26,599 --> 00:29:29,560
I didn't know
he wanted to be captain.

554
00:29:32,229 --> 00:29:34,523
Bora kind of mentioned

555
00:29:34,899 --> 00:29:37,485
that Hugo asked to be captain.

556
00:29:37,568 --> 00:29:40,029
But, as I understood,

557
00:29:40,571 --> 00:29:43,532
Bora said he chose me as captain

558
00:29:43,616 --> 00:29:46,577
and the rest of the team
chose me as captain.

559
00:29:47,119 --> 00:29:49,497
{\an8}The decision to make
Tomas Boy captain

560
00:29:49,580 --> 00:29:51,832
{\an8}becomes a diplomatic move

561
00:29:51,916 --> 00:29:55,169
{\an8}from Bora Milutinovic,
to avoid another kind

562
00:29:55,252 --> 00:29:57,087
<i>of issue.</i>

563
00:29:57,171 --> 00:29:59,507
<i>He chooses a talented guy
with leadership,</i>

564
00:29:59,590 --> 00:30:02,301
which is what you need

565
00:30:02,384 --> 00:30:04,345
to carry the captain band.

566
00:30:04,553 --> 00:30:08,349
{\an8}They're all the same to me.

567
00:30:08,432 --> 00:30:11,727
{\an8}Tomas Boy had a lot of merits.

568
00:30:11,810 --> 00:30:14,688
He is captain.
Hugo is third.

569
00:30:15,022 --> 00:30:18,776
Hugo never protested against it.

570
00:30:18,943 --> 00:30:20,444
What does that show?

571
00:30:20,528 --> 00:30:22,446
That the team was important to him,

572
00:30:22,530 --> 00:30:24,782
the team's spirit,

573
00:30:24,865 --> 00:30:26,742
no matter who was captain.

574
00:30:26,825 --> 00:30:29,119
<i>Later I knew that he thought,</i>

575
00:30:29,203 --> 00:30:30,996
<i>since Maradona had been chosen</i>

576
00:30:31,080 --> 00:30:33,999
by his great Argentinian colleagues,

577
00:30:34,083 --> 00:30:35,709
he had to be chosen too,

578
00:30:35,793 --> 00:30:37,127
like him.

579
00:30:37,211 --> 00:30:38,879
{\an8}I didn't get that part.

580
00:30:39,046 --> 00:30:40,005
{\an8}No.

581
00:30:40,089 --> 00:30:41,465
{\an8}It's not like,

582
00:30:41,549 --> 00:30:43,676
"Stop pretending, Tomas."

583
00:30:43,759 --> 00:30:45,261
They always think that.

584
00:30:46,095 --> 00:30:49,014
I never knew
he wanted to be captain.

585
00:30:49,848 --> 00:30:52,560
"Being captain or not,

586
00:30:53,018 --> 00:30:55,229
it doesn't matter to me.

587
00:30:55,312 --> 00:30:58,065
But their way of thinking
is really sad.

588
00:30:58,315 --> 00:31:01,068
They have a mediocre mentality."

589
00:31:12,204 --> 00:31:16,208
<i>The Coca Cola company
made an important</i>

590
00:31:16,292 --> 00:31:19,128
<i>where there was a minute left
and Hugo Sanchez</i>

591
00:31:19,211 --> 00:31:20,588
shot a penalty and scored.

592
00:31:20,838 --> 00:31:22,506
And he played against Paraguay,

593
00:31:22,923 --> 00:31:25,634
there's a minute left,
it's made for TV.

594
00:31:25,718 --> 00:31:27,177
<i>I ran because we went live</i>

595
00:31:27,219 --> 00:31:31,515
<i>and I go out, there's a stand,
Coca Cola and the shot.</i>

596
00:31:31,599 --> 00:31:34,852
<i>Hugo Sanchez was that ad
in front of my eyes</i>

597
00:31:34,935 --> 00:31:36,604
<i>with a different ending.</i>

598
00:31:37,104 --> 00:31:38,981
I remember Hugo took the ball.

599
00:31:39,064 --> 00:31:41,066
{\an8}Aguirre could have shot,
Tomas could have shot,

600
00:31:41,233 --> 00:31:43,527
{\an8}I could have shot, Luis Flores,

601
00:31:43,611 --> 00:31:45,112
{\an8}if he was there, I forgot.

602
00:31:45,404 --> 00:31:47,281
<i>But the important thing</i>

603
00:31:47,364 --> 00:31:49,867
<i>is the confidence
to stand up in there.</i>

604
00:31:49,950 --> 00:31:51,285
<i>Not anyone does it.</i>

605
00:31:54,121 --> 00:31:55,623
<i>When I failed at that time</i>

606
00:31:57,041 --> 00:31:58,334
<i>and it was a tie,</i>

607
00:31:59,710 --> 00:32:00,794
I felt human.

608
00:32:02,880 --> 00:32:05,257
<i>How would you feel
when a player like Luis Flores,</i>

609
00:32:05,716 --> 00:32:07,760
<i>is told, "Go to the bench,</i>

610
00:32:07,843 --> 00:32:09,261
<i>because Hugo Sanchez
is taking your place"?</i>

611
00:32:09,470 --> 00:32:10,554
<i>Imagine.</i>

612
00:32:10,638 --> 00:32:13,641
I'm not ousting anyone.

613
00:32:13,724 --> 00:32:16,685
I'm part of a 22 players list.

614
00:32:16,727 --> 00:32:19,271
A process that takes up
many years,

615
00:32:19,355 --> 00:32:22,191
and there's a decision
that leaves you out.

616
00:32:22,358 --> 00:32:23,734
<i>You'll be starting?</i>

617
00:32:24,234 --> 00:32:26,987
That depends on the coach.

618
00:32:27,071 --> 00:32:30,783
<i>They will hang Bora
in Mexico City's Zocalo.</i>

619
00:32:30,991 --> 00:32:31,825
Exactly.

620
00:32:31,909 --> 00:32:34,703
He will assume that responsibility

621
00:32:34,953 --> 00:32:39,249
and he will take the risk,
if that happens.

622
00:32:40,376 --> 00:32:42,378
<i>We played the fifth game
against Germany.</i>

623
00:32:43,545 --> 00:32:44,588
<i>We played really well.</i>

624
00:32:45,506 --> 00:32:47,007
<i>We had many chances to score.
The Colombian referee</i>

625
00:32:47,091 --> 00:32:49,677
<i>canceled my goal,
Aguirre was really close.</i>

626
00:32:50,302 --> 00:32:52,513
<i>When we get to penalties,</i>

627
00:32:52,596 --> 00:32:56,183
<i>none of us believed
that we would arrive to that.</i>

628
00:32:56,266 --> 00:32:59,812
{\an8}<i>When Bora asked, "Who's shooting"
Nobody stepped in.</i>

629
00:33:00,771 --> 00:33:02,523
<i>Everyone cramped.
Tomas cramped.</i>

630
00:33:02,606 --> 00:33:04,817
<i>Quirarte cramped.
Hugo Sanchez cramped.</i>

631
00:33:04,900 --> 00:33:06,193
{\an8}Nobody shot the penalties.

632
00:33:06,276 --> 00:33:07,945
{\an8}They look like defenses
shooting penalties

633
00:33:08,028 --> 00:33:09,780
<i>in front of a goalkeeper
like Schumacher.</i>

634
00:33:16,537 --> 00:33:19,498
<i>The possibility of Hugo
reversed what he had done</i>

635
00:33:19,581 --> 00:33:22,000
{\an8}in that World Cup,
shooting the penalty

636
00:33:22,084 --> 00:33:25,629
{\an8}and scoring, helping Mexico
to go over Germany,

637
00:33:25,713 --> 00:33:27,339
{\an8}would have changed
the rest of History.

638
00:33:27,506 --> 00:33:29,258
Despite that,

639
00:33:30,092 --> 00:33:32,302
{\an8}from my outside point of view,

640
00:33:32,511 --> 00:33:34,388
{\an8}as a journalist that watches the Cup

641
00:33:34,471 --> 00:33:37,808
and broadcasts it,
I always saw him

642
00:33:37,933 --> 00:33:39,810
<i>give his all in the World Cup.</i>

643
00:33:41,228 --> 00:33:43,188
<i>The World Cup is also politics.</i>

644
00:33:43,689 --> 00:33:44,732
<i>They always say,</i>

645
00:33:44,815 --> 00:33:47,735
<i>"The referee helped the local team,
because they're local".</i>

646
00:33:47,860 --> 00:33:50,070
{\an8}<i>But the referee didn't help here.</i>

647
00:33:50,154 --> 00:33:51,822
{\an8}<i>Mexico didn't help itself</i>

648
00:33:51,905 --> 00:33:55,367
{\an8}<i>protecting its own interests
since the schedule design.</i>

649
00:33:55,826 --> 00:33:58,370
Who always has the preference?
The local.

650
00:33:59,037 --> 00:34:01,165
It wasn't the players' fault,

651
00:34:01,248 --> 00:34:03,292
nor Bora's, nor Hugo's,
nor anyone else's.

652
00:34:03,459 --> 00:34:05,335
You just take them out
of their fortress,

653
00:34:05,419 --> 00:34:07,045
<i>the Aztec,
and they become vulnerable.</i>

654
00:34:17,723 --> 00:34:21,518
Any player
who performs below expectations

655
00:34:21,602 --> 00:34:24,438
gets disproportionate criticism.

656
00:34:24,646 --> 00:34:29,151
<i>And no one garnered more expectation
than Hugo Sanchez in Mexico.</i>

657
00:34:34,448 --> 00:34:35,991
<i>I met Isabel,</i>

658
00:34:36,408 --> 00:34:39,036
<i>my current wife, in '90.
It was love at first sight</i>

659
00:34:39,119 --> 00:34:42,873
<i>and we haven't been apart since.</i>

660
00:34:43,999 --> 00:34:48,128
Hugo made me feel the most
wonderful person in the world.

661
00:34:48,295 --> 00:34:49,671
{\an8}I was a princess

662
00:34:50,088 --> 00:34:53,091
{\an8}and all he wanted was
that I was happy.

663
00:34:53,175 --> 00:34:55,761
{\an8}The rest of the world
disappeared for a while.

664
00:34:56,094 --> 00:34:57,596
<i>Hugo is very protective.</i>

665
00:34:57,679 --> 00:35:00,682
The priest that married us
came at the end of the ceremony

666
00:35:00,766 --> 00:35:01,892
to say goodbye,

667
00:35:01,975 --> 00:35:04,853
and he says,
"What's your problem? She's my wife.

668
00:35:05,312 --> 00:35:06,396
Why are you talking to her?"

669
00:35:06,730 --> 00:35:08,816
And he says, "Sorry, Hugo!

670
00:35:08,899 --> 00:35:10,567
I was just saying goodbye."

671
00:35:10,651 --> 00:35:12,611
"I'm sorry, but she's my wife."

672
00:35:12,903 --> 00:35:14,947
You can't be jealous
of the priest

673
00:35:15,030 --> 00:35:16,281
that just married her.

674
00:35:18,867 --> 00:35:20,035
<i>We waited a few years,</i>

675
00:35:20,118 --> 00:35:23,288
<i>to enjoy a childless marriage</i>

676
00:35:23,747 --> 00:35:26,250
<i>until she got pregnant.
And,</i>

677
00:35:26,834 --> 00:35:29,586
<i>thank God, they were two.</i>

678
00:35:29,753 --> 00:35:30,796
<i>Isabela and Hana.</i>

679
00:35:31,964 --> 00:35:36,343
I was lucky to find him at a time

680
00:35:36,969 --> 00:35:41,390
when he had practically achieved
everything he ever dreamed of.

681
00:35:41,723 --> 00:35:43,934
<i>Imagine the euphoria.</i>

682
00:35:44,309 --> 00:35:47,312
<i>He was conquering the world,
at that time</i>

683
00:35:47,479 --> 00:35:49,314
<i>it belonged to him.
He was the center</i>

684
00:35:49,481 --> 00:35:51,024
<i>because, in football,</i>

685
00:35:51,108 --> 00:35:53,151
<i>being Real Madrid's center forward</i>

686
00:35:53,235 --> 00:35:54,820
<i>is the center of the world.</i>

687
00:35:55,320 --> 00:35:58,282
<i>He was that back then
and he was scoring</i>

688
00:35:58,365 --> 00:36:01,243
<i>two or three goals every week.</i>

689
00:36:01,910 --> 00:36:05,497
He felt that rush you get
when you do everything right.

690
00:36:05,581 --> 00:36:08,125
When things you thought of doing
turn out right.

691
00:36:08,584 --> 00:36:11,837
<i>He had the traits of a born winner,</i>

692
00:36:12,337 --> 00:36:14,965
and he fundamentally showed
the ambition,

693
00:36:15,048 --> 00:36:18,218
{\an8}a determination out of the ordinary.

694
00:36:18,302 --> 00:36:19,469
I confronted Hugo

695
00:36:19,553 --> 00:36:23,056
and he had no friends.

696
00:36:23,140 --> 00:36:24,683
He was a

697
00:36:24,933 --> 00:36:27,144
killer.
If he had to step on you,

698
00:36:27,227 --> 00:36:29,521
elbow you,
spit on you, threaten you

699
00:36:29,771 --> 00:36:32,482
<i>and score, he would.
He had no remorse.</i>

700
00:36:33,817 --> 00:36:37,613
{\an8}Many of the things he accomplished

701
00:36:37,821 --> 00:36:40,240
{\an8}were because he said,
"I'll be the best."

702
00:36:40,449 --> 00:36:42,326
{\an8}When you say,
"I'm the best one here,

703
00:36:42,409 --> 00:36:43,201
<i>or I want to be
or will be the best,</i>

704
00:36:43,285 --> 00:36:44,536
<i>or I'm the best,"</i>

705
00:36:44,620 --> 00:36:48,332
<i>it seems wrong, it hurts</i>

706
00:36:48,624 --> 00:36:52,377
<i>and we vent national miseries
that burden us.</i>

707
00:36:53,837 --> 00:36:55,297
Since I was a child, I didn't

708
00:36:56,381 --> 00:36:59,343
have such a strong personality,
temper,

709
00:37:00,260 --> 00:37:03,972
but when I became a pro
ad went to Spain

710
00:37:04,264 --> 00:37:07,100
<i>and I lived outside my country,</i>

711
00:37:07,184 --> 00:37:09,978
<i>away from my surroundings,
my family, my friends,</i>

