00:54:13,209 --> 00:54:15,753
<i>was me trying to convince him</i>

1023
00:54:15,836 --> 00:54:18,673
<i>to be more daring.
"Think it through.</i>

1024
00:54:18,756 --> 00:54:20,174
I have to come in as forward

1025
00:54:20,257 --> 00:54:23,052
to score the goals
and win the game."

1026
00:54:23,970 --> 00:54:25,513
"You know what?
I'd like it too

1027
00:54:25,596 --> 00:54:27,765
if you came as center forward,
but right now,

1028
00:54:28,307 --> 00:54:29,892
if I leave midfield,

1029
00:54:29,976 --> 00:54:32,019
we're standing against
a very good team

1030
00:54:32,561 --> 00:54:33,896
and we'll be in trouble."

1031
00:54:34,397 --> 00:54:35,856
"But keep warming up."

1032
00:54:35,940 --> 00:54:37,817
I then decided
he wouldn't get in.

1033
00:54:38,651 --> 00:54:41,153
He comes back five
or three minutes later

1034
00:54:41,362 --> 00:54:43,114
and says, "Hugo won't play.

1035
00:54:43,906 --> 00:54:45,032
Period."

1036
00:54:45,116 --> 00:54:46,867
You enter as midfield
and move forward.

1037
00:54:47,243 --> 00:54:49,203
The player rules the field.

1038
00:54:49,412 --> 00:54:51,080
"I'll enter midfield."
"Yes."

1039
00:54:51,163 --> 00:54:52,832
"You go back, I go forward."

1040
00:54:52,915 --> 00:54:56,127
But a center forward
was missing.

1041
00:54:56,210 --> 00:54:58,129
I'm completely convinced.

1042
00:54:58,629 --> 00:55:01,882
That's what the whole
country was clamoring.

1043
00:55:14,603 --> 00:55:18,065
<i>The Mexicans said,
"Isabel, what's wrong?</i>

1044
00:55:18,149 --> 00:55:20,568
<i>Tell Hugo to come out."
You know the Mexicans.</i>

1045
00:55:21,193 --> 00:55:23,612
I was like, "What can I do?"

1046
00:55:23,696 --> 00:55:25,698
"You tell him!
Sure you can."

1047
00:55:25,781 --> 00:55:27,283
"Tell Miguel."

1048
00:55:27,783 --> 00:55:31,287
<i>And, sadly, for many fans</i>

1049
00:55:31,370 --> 00:55:33,497
and for the football world

1050
00:55:33,581 --> 00:55:36,333
the only one who could decide

1051
00:55:36,417 --> 00:55:37,710
at that time was I,
and I exerted that power.

1052
00:55:38,711 --> 00:55:41,380
He didn't come out.

1053
00:55:42,173 --> 00:55:45,885
<i>It was one of the saddest episodes
in Mexican football,</i>

1054
00:55:45,968 --> 00:55:49,346
{\an8}because we felt we had the man

1055
00:55:49,430 --> 00:55:50,347
{\an8}that could take us

1056
00:55:50,431 --> 00:55:55,436
{\an8}to the next desired round...

1057
00:56:01,442 --> 00:56:03,569
{\an8}<i>Football generates, during games,</i>

1058
00:56:03,652 --> 00:56:04,862
{\an8}<i>many scenarios.</i>

1059
00:56:04,945 --> 00:56:07,156
One of the most important
it generates

1060
00:56:07,239 --> 00:56:09,700
is what you can provoke
in your rival

1061
00:56:09,784 --> 00:56:11,118
with the players you have.

1062
00:56:11,786 --> 00:56:14,413
<i>Don't get the player in,
get his name in,</i>

1063
00:56:14,538 --> 00:56:17,333
<i>and you disturb them.
That was the dilemma.</i>

1064
00:56:17,583 --> 00:56:20,461
Maybe Miguel Mejia Baron
did it to take care of him.

1065
00:56:21,128 --> 00:56:22,213
Who knows.

1066
00:56:22,463 --> 00:56:24,340
<i>To bring Hugo in,</i>

1067
00:56:25,007 --> 00:56:26,133
<i>as people think,</i>

1068
00:56:26,217 --> 00:56:29,220
<i>just to kick a penalty</i>

1069
00:56:29,637 --> 00:56:30,971
<i>is ridiculous.</i>

1070
00:56:31,263 --> 00:56:32,681
<i>Not because he can't.</i>

1071
00:56:33,265 --> 00:56:34,183
<i>Ridiculous</i>

1072
00:56:34,266 --> 00:56:36,936
{\an8}<i>because he shot his last penalty</i>

1073
00:56:37,019 --> 00:56:39,271
{\an8}<i>with his team Rayo Vallecano
and he failed,</i>

1074
00:56:39,355 --> 00:56:41,398
and his team went
to Second Division.

1075
00:56:41,482 --> 00:56:42,942
That was his last penalty.

1076
00:56:43,818 --> 00:56:45,694
I saw the Paraguay one,

1077
00:56:46,779 --> 00:56:48,405
in '86.

1078
00:56:48,781 --> 00:56:52,118
I lived the moment
when Hugo told Bora,

1079
00:56:52,201 --> 00:56:53,244
"I have cramps against Germany."

1080
00:56:53,327 --> 00:56:54,829
At that time,
everything came over me

