00:56:55,121 --> 00:56:57,957
<i>and I thought,
"Why should I bring him in?"</i>

1082
00:56:58,833 --> 00:57:02,753
<i>Such a big responsibility,
just to do that.</i>

1083
00:57:03,712 --> 00:57:06,173
<i>I thought all those things
and said,</i>

1084
00:57:06,382 --> 00:57:08,217
<i>"Not even for penalties."</i>

1085
00:57:08,509 --> 00:57:09,844
I meant no disrespect.

1086
00:57:09,927 --> 00:57:12,096
It was a coaching decision
in a given time.

1087
00:57:12,388 --> 00:57:14,723
<i>If he had wanted to come in,</i>

1088
00:57:15,099 --> 00:57:17,977
<i>of course we would have won,
just for his presence.</i>

1089
00:57:19,019 --> 00:57:21,480
Not because he'd have scored
three of four goals.

1090
00:57:21,605 --> 00:57:24,233
Hugo's presence in the field,

1091
00:57:24,525 --> 00:57:25,234
in the penalties,

1092
00:57:25,317 --> 00:57:27,278
he would have been
the first shooter

1093
00:57:27,611 --> 00:57:30,281
and we would have felt confident.

1094
00:57:30,364 --> 00:57:31,532
Maybe...

1095
00:57:31,824 --> 00:57:34,243
I should have seen before Miguel.

1096
00:57:35,286 --> 00:57:37,580
He asked me if Hugo...

1097
00:57:37,663 --> 00:57:39,874
I said, "It's unnecessary."

1098
00:57:40,583 --> 00:57:42,126
<i>I didn't promise him anything.</i>

1099
00:57:43,085 --> 00:57:44,211
<i>I had no obligations.</i>

1100
00:57:44,295 --> 00:57:45,838
<i>He and I had obligations
as sportsmen</i>

1101
00:57:45,921 --> 00:57:48,090
<i>that represented Mexico,
